in Southern Sri Lanka.

00:00:20.324 --> 00:00:22.283
They're gonna cook for us a home-cooked,

00:00:22.283 --> 00:00:25.183
everything cooked traditional
over fire in clay pots.

00:00:25.183 --> 00:00:27.023
We're gonna have a lot of fun.

00:00:27.023 --> 00:00:30.743
We're gonna eat a lot of
delicious, incredible food today.

00:00:30.743 --> 00:00:33.326
(upbeat music)

00:00:41.133 --> 00:00:41.966
Good, how are you?

00:00:41.966 --> 00:00:42.799
- Good, good, good.

00:00:42.799 --> 00:00:43.632
- [Mark] Good to see you again.

00:00:43.632 --> 00:00:44.547
We got here a little bit early,

00:00:44.547 --> 00:00:46.487
but they have already started cooking

00:00:46.487 --> 00:00:49.717
some of the traditional dishes
from Southern Sri Lanka.

00:00:49.717 --> 00:00:51.998
This is a beautiful tropical compound.

00:00:51.998 --> 00:00:56.877
The Nelson family, they own
and operate a wood mill.

00:00:56.877 --> 00:01:00.457
So there's logs; they're
making planks of wood.

00:01:00.457 --> 00:01:03.897
It's gonna be all outside,
everything cooked over fire.

00:01:03.897 --> 00:01:05.998
You can already smell
the spices in the air.

00:01:05.998 --> 00:01:09.517
And then Aunty is in charge
of cooking in the back.

00:01:09.517 --> 00:01:11.017
- They have an open gas stove,

