and also they have the old-fashioned one--

00:01:12.487 --> 00:01:13.485
- I'm lost.

00:01:13.485 --> 00:01:14.727
Awesome.

00:01:14.727 --> 00:01:15.644
Fire stove.

00:01:17.685 --> 00:01:20.285
(bubbling)

00:01:20.285 --> 00:01:21.452
Mango chutney.

00:01:22.387 --> 00:01:23.220
- Try one.

00:01:23.220 --> 00:01:24.098
- Amazing, okay, cool.

00:01:24.098 --> 00:01:27.157
And then they have the
mango chutney prepared.

00:01:27.157 --> 00:01:30.407
The family is very well known for this.

00:01:32.230 --> 00:01:33.063
Oh, wow.

00:01:33.993 --> 00:01:36.487
Oh, it's awesome man.

00:01:36.487 --> 00:01:37.629
It's so good.
- Balance of flavor, right?

00:01:37.629 --> 00:01:41.379
- Dude, it's sweet, a
little bit spicy, sour.

00:01:48.403 --> 00:01:50.653
(bubbling)

00:01:52.768 --> 00:01:54.476
- This is a tuna curry.

00:01:54.476 --> 00:01:56.757
- [Mark] Wow, smells and dishes going,

00:01:56.757 --> 00:01:58.467
so outside they're cooking dishes too.

00:01:58.467 --> 00:01:59.689
There's a fish curry going.

00:01:59.689 --> 00:02:01.317
There's shrimp that simmering down

00:02:01.317 --> 00:02:02.815
with some herbs and spices.

00:02:02.815 --> 00:02:04.883
The aromas, the steam, the cooking,

00:02:04.883 --> 00:02:06.548
everything is cooked traditional,

00:02:06.548 --> 00:02:10.158
and most dishes are cooked
in clay pots over fire.

00:02:10.158 --> 00:02:12.840
The clay pots just build up the flavor

00:02:12.840 --> 00:02:14.299
and keep using the clay pots.

00:02:14.299 --> 00:02:17.708
That's one of the traditional
ways of cooking in Sri Lanka.

00:02:17.708 --> 00:02:21.541
This is going to be a
feast that I can't wait.

00:02:23.187 --> 00:02:27.011
The whole chair on it, that's awesome.

00:02:27.011 --> 00:02:29.831
(laughs)

00:02:29.831 --> 00:02:32.751
Coconut milk and shredded coconut
is an essential ingredient

00:02:32.751 --> 00:02:34.711
in Sri Lankan food and cooking.

00:02:34.711 --> 00:02:36.251
And they, often times I've just seen

00:02:36.251 --> 00:02:37.651
the traditional coconut shredder

00:02:37.651 --> 00:02:39.571
just on a little wooden stool,

00:02:39.571 --> 00:02:41.290
but this is the deluxe version.

00:02:41.290 --> 00:02:42.751
It's on an office chair.

00:02:42.751 --> 00:02:44.881
Then over there, she is
slicing the gotu kola,

00:02:44.881 --> 00:02:47.193
which is in English it's pennywort leaves.

00:02:47.193 --> 00:02:49.460
I remember that from my
last trip to Sri Lanka.

00:02:49.460 --> 00:02:52.820
It's a really green, really healthy,

00:02:52.820 --> 00:02:55.070
really earthy tasting herb.

00:02:56.521 --> 00:02:57.503
Really good.

00:02:57.503 --> 00:02:58.336
Brinjal curry?

00:02:58.336 --> 00:02:59.248
- Moju, moju.

00:02:59.248 --> 00:03:00.415
- It has moju.

00:03:01.405 --> 00:03:02.580
- [Mark] The eggplant, right?

00:03:02.580 --> 00:03:04.291
Brinjal, brinjal.

00:03:04.291 --> 00:03:06.726
- It's not processed, right?

00:03:06.726 --> 00:03:09.276
Its with goraka which is--

00:03:09.276 --> 00:03:11.499
- Let's have a taste.

00:03:11.499 --> 00:03:12.732
- [Mark] It's okay to taste?

00:03:12.732 --> 00:03:14.113
- [Ucith] Yeah

00:03:14.113 --> 00:03:16.020
- [Mark] This piece?

00:03:16.020 --> 00:03:17.359
- [Aunty] Very spicy, okay?

00:03:17.359 --> 00:03:18.442
- [Mark] Okay

00:03:20.062 --> 00:03:22.895
(foreign chatter)

00:03:27.455 --> 00:03:31.758
- This is a fish curry with
garcinia, and then spices.

00:03:31.758 --> 00:03:34.026
There's curry leaves in
it, there's chillies in it.

00:03:34.026 --> 00:03:37.227
This is our favorite
of many in this region.

00:03:37.227 --> 00:03:38.569
And it's specifically a Southern--

00:03:38.569 --> 00:03:39.852
- [Ucith] She makes it the
best out of the family,

00:03:39.852 --> 00:03:41.473
so we come all the way
here to justify that.

00:03:41.473 --> 00:03:43.147
- Aunty makes it the best.

00:03:43.147 --> 00:03:45.210
- [Ucith] The longer you keep
it the better the flavors.

00:03:45.210 --> 00:03:47.220
- Oh, because of the?

00:03:47.220 --> 00:03:49.121
(indistinct)

00:03:49.121 --> 00:03:50.929
- And it's sour.

00:03:50.929 --> 00:03:52.281
- Ah, because that's the garcinia.

00:03:52.281 --> 00:03:54.005
It's very sour, right?
- Right.

00:03:54.005 --> 00:03:55.348
- It's a very sour fish.

00:03:55.348 --> 00:03:57.413
Okay, taste testing.

00:03:57.413 --> 00:03:59.657
(upbeat music)

00:03:59.657 --> 00:04:02.897
Ah yeah, mmm, that's wonderful.

00:04:02.897 --> 00:04:06.018
Ah, there's black pepper in there, too.

00:04:06.018 --> 00:04:08.288
You taste the black pepper,
you taste the sourness,

00:04:08.288 --> 00:04:11.725
Ooh, the sourness
actually keeps on coming.

00:04:11.725 --> 00:04:14.692
And Ucith says that adding some
coconut balances the flavor.

00:04:14.692 --> 00:04:16.882
So that's the fresh grated
coconut on top of that.

00:04:16.882 --> 00:04:19.465
(upbeat music)

00:04:23.241 --> 00:04:24.416
- Oh wow!

00:04:24.416 --> 00:04:25.833
That is stunning.

00:04:26.807 --> 00:04:27.945
That is flavor.

00:04:27.945 --> 00:04:30.862
- [Chef] The coconut milk is fresh.

00:04:38.738 --> 00:04:41.130
- It smells incredible.

00:04:41.130 --> 00:04:44.205
This is just an incredible
tropical paradise.

00:04:44.205 --> 00:04:46.844
The greenery, the fruits, the vegetables,

00:04:46.844 --> 00:04:48.203
and herbs and spices.

00:04:48.203 --> 00:04:50.384
It's, oh man, coconuts are just blooming.

00:04:50.384 --> 00:04:51.217
Prawns are done?

